From: Dong Aisheng <aisheng.dong@nxp.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Nov 2017 16:55:08 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2961/5242] MLK-17074-6 soc: imx8: pm-domains: use state_idx
 to distinguish the low power state

commit  22480166717bfbab012b35a06510767e7173be99 from
https://source.codeaurora.org/external/imx/linux-imx.git

Use state_idx to distinguish the low power state.

Reviewed-by: Frank Li <frank.li@nxp.com>
Reviewed-by: Ranjani Vaidyanathan <Ranjani.Vaidyanathan@nxp.com>
Signed-off-by: Dong Aisheng <aisheng.dong@nxp.com>
Signed-off-by: Meng Li <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/soc/imx/pm-domains.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/soc/imx/pm-domains.c b/drivers/soc/imx/pm-domains.c
index aa99a18..e5dc8d5 100644
--- a/drivers/soc/imx/pm-domains.c
+++ b/drivers/soc/imx/pm-domains.c
@@ -69,7 +69,7 @@ static int imx8_pd_power(struct generic_pm_domain *domain, bool power_on)
 
 	sci_err = sc_pm_set_resource_power_mode(pm_ipc_handle, pd->rsrc_id,
 		(power_on) ? SC_PM_PW_MODE_ON :
-		(pd->runtime_idle_active) ? SC_PM_PW_MODE_LP : SC_PM_PW_MODE_OFF);
+		pd->pd.state_idx ? SC_PM_PW_MODE_OFF : SC_PM_PW_MODE_LP);
 	if (sci_err)
 		pr_err("Failed power operation on resource %d\n", pd->rsrc_id);
 
